Nam Spoletinus] ⁴ For as to the case of T. Matrinius of Spoletium.’ Matrinius belonged to a Latina colonia. Spoletium (Spoleto) was in Umbria. The Colonia was settled ss.c. 241.

The Lex Apuleia was one of the several leges proposed by the tribune L. Apuleius Saturninus. We know no more of this Lex than what Cicero tells us, and what is con- tained in a passage of Aurelius Victor (De Viris Illustr. c. 73), who says that Saturni- nus designed to send colonists to Sicily, Achaia, and Macedonia. Victor also speaks of a proposal by Saturninus to give to Ma- rius’ veterans 005 hundred ‘ jugera ’ each in Africa.
